Per Dr. Ray Peat, the easiest thing to try if you get one of those wildcard rashes from yard work or after a long hike through various grasses is to just fill a bathtub with warm water and dump 1 lbs. of salt and 1 lbs. of baking soda into it and then soak for like an hour or so.

It's 2-3 times more concentrated in terms of osmolarity than seawater. There was one French medic injecting something similar into patients' veins after draining blood out to extend their lifespans and cure cancer and stuff. But do not inject the bathtub stuff. Just soak into it.

Dr. Ray Peat noted women tend to have a more "global" consciousness and it is easy to notice that women everywhere tend to be more similar to each other than men are. It's not hard to imagine yourself even with a woman from 1000 years ago without there being such a big difference

This all occurred to me because I saw a picture on 4chan of a bunch of people literally roleplaying with plastic swords and stuff in a forest and it struck me that even though the men looked ridiculous the one girl still looked alluring because she was "universal" in spite of it.

Men are more particular across space and time both. Which is why lower female "kidnapped by time machine Tarzan" type erotica is always fetishistic. An opposite way would be unremarkable because it wouldn't be that different from a regular relationship with someone from your town

Seeing the still-orange moon rise low in the horizon behind the tree leaves always makes you think there is a forest fire or an arson or a faraway bonfire or so going on there. But no. It's just the moon again. I wonder if the moon can ever flash green like the sun. Probably not.
